Armstrong]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2018}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Greatest Hits\n| type       = greatest\n| artist     = [[Dido (singer)|Dido]]\n| cover      = Greatesthitsdido.jpg\n| border     = yes\n| alt        =\n| released   = {{start date|2013|11|22|df=y}}\n| recorded   = 1999\u20132013\n| studio     =\n| genre      = <!--Do not add unsourced genres -->\n| length     = {{duration|m=76|s=21}}\n| label      = [[RCA Records|RCA]]\n| producer   = {{hlist|[[Dido (singer)|Dido]]|[[Rollo Armstrong|Rollo]]|[[Rick Nowels]]|John Harrison|[[Mike Hedges]]|[[Jon Brion]]|The Ark|[[Brian Eno]]|[[Sister Bliss]]|[[Greg Kurstin]]|[[DJ Mark the 45 King|The 45 King]]|[[A. R. Rahman]]}}\n| prev_title = [[Girl Who Got Away]]\n| prev_year  = 2013\n| next_title = [[Still on My Mind]]\n| next_year  = 2019\n}}\n\n'''''Greatest Hits''''' is a greatest hits album by British singer-songwriter [[Dido (singer)|Dido]] released in 2013. The album compiles all of Dido's singles since her first album ''[[No Angel (album)|No Angel]]'' (1999), through to her latest material, ''[[Girl Who Got Away]]'' (2013). The two-disc collection was released on 22 November 2013 in Ireland, and includes a new track, \"NYC\", as well as a collection of remixes and collaborations. The track listing was confirmed on 9 October 2013.<ref>https://www.facebook.com/#!/photo.php?fbid=10151954735587905&set=a.10151152512347905.493258.19571497904&type=1&theater</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\nCredits adapted from the album's [[liner notes]]<ref name=\"Album booklet\">{{cite AV media notes|others = Dido |title = Greatest Hits |year = 2013 |type = booklet |publisher = [[RCA Records|RCA]]}}</ref>\n{{Track listing\n| headline = ''Greatest Hits'' \u2013 {{nobold|Standard edition}}\n| extra_column = Producer(s)\n| title_width = 40%\n| writing_width = 35%\n| extra_width = 25%\n| total_length = 1:16:21\n\n| title1 = [[Here with Me (Dido song)|Here with Me]]\n| note1 = from ''[[No Angel (album)|No Angel]]'